                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d310">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.2221/1138: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Seville</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bay</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seville</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-08-26T11:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 26, 1938—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 26—8:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>55. Department’s 44, August 19, 6 p.m.<note n="91" xml:id="d310fn91">See footnote
                        90, <ref target="#pg_318">p. 318</ref>.</note> Señor Vidal stated over
                    telephone last evening that if I would write him about the proposal of Friends
                    of the Abraham Lincoln Brigade he would make a reply. A personal note will
                    suffice. Instruction requested.<note n="92" xml:id="d310fn92">Department’s
                        telegram No. 46, August 27, 2 p.m., in reply, stated: “Personal note
                        approved.” (852.2221/1064)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bay</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
